      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:2:66:3",
      "text": [
        " إِذَا وَالَى الرَّجُلُ الرَّجُلَ فَلَهُ مِيرَاثُهُ وَ عَلَيْهِ مَعْقُلَتُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazaan, altogether from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When the man is the guardian of the man, so for him is his inheritance and upon him is his wergild’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father and Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan from all from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn Salim who has narrated the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘When a man is under the guardianship of a man for him is his legacy and on him is the liability for wergild.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
